 function of the secondary yolk sac during human development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Forms primitive blood cells and germ cells","Creates a fluid-filled cavity for embryo protection","Develops into the placenta","Produces amniotic fluid","Facilitates gas exchange for the embryo"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eforms primitive blood cells and germ cells\u003C/strong\u003E during weeks 4-7 of development. It is the primary site of early hematopoiesis and is crucial for the formation and migration of primordial germ cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreates a fluid-filled cavity for embryo protection\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the function of the amniotic cavity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelops into the placenta\u003C/strong\u003E - The placenta develops from the chorion, not the yolk sac\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProduces amniotic fluid\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a function of the amniotic membrane and maternal serum filtration\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFacilitates gas exchange for the embryo\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily a function of the placenta after its formation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe secondary yolk sac also produces important proteins including alpha-fetoprotein and transferrin which are essential for early embryonic development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The secondary yolk sac is crucial for early hematopoiesis and primordial germ cell formation during weeks 4-7 of human development","The secondary yolk sac produces proteins essential for early embryonic development including alpha-fetoprotein and transferrin","Unlike in birds and reptiles, the 